pseudo selectors:
	span[class~="sr-only"] select any span includes sr-only
    clip: rect(50px,50px,50px,50px); forms a rectangle around element
    clip-path:inset(59%); koliko posto kvadrata je ispinjeno
    
    :first-of-type pseudo-selector is used to target the first element that matches the selector. 
    :last-of-type
    .line:nth-of-type(2)
    calc() function is a CSS function that allows you to calculate a value based on other values.  calc(1.25rem + 2px) 
    
    !important to prop to cant overwrite it 
    
    
    span[class~="sr-only"] {  ====> to hide an element;
      border: 0;  
      clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);
      clip-path: inset(50%);
      height: 1px;
      width: 1px;
      overflow: hidden;
      white-space: nowrap;
      position:absolute;
      padding: 0;
      margin:-1px;
      
    }

